data.title: Frendx 1983 12
data.meta_description: FRENDX-1983-12 - Free download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. The North American Shortwave Association has provided information about shortwave radio since 1961. The club focuses on domestic and international broadcasts on shortwave frequencies between 2 and 30 MHz. NASWA considers itself to be the premiere organization in North America for shortwave listeners and DXers. The club publication, "Frendx" (later called "The Journal") has been published since the club's beginning.
